issues.body:
Issues #19647, #22604 and #29071 centered around how slow NumPy's einsum is compared to other libraries. The last issue to use BLAS even when `optimize=False` became a [branch](https://github.com/lysnikolaou/numpy/tree/use-blas-even-if-nooptimize) but did not become a PR because the heuristics proved difficult to tune.

Rather than try to guess what is better, perhaps we could allow the user to force using BLAS with a new kwarg? This would be "safe" in terms of performance as it would allow the user to choose. It seems #23513 will speed up the `optimize=True` case, but the kwarg would allow users of intermediate-sized arrays to get BLAS threading speedups even when using `optimize=False`.

@jcmgray, as someone who has put a lot of effort into einsum, would there be use-cases where `optimize=False, use_blas=True` could improve performance over `optimize=True`?
